deck: Raymonde is Jean-Paul Beaubier´s friend.
description:
Raymonde Belmonde owned a small shop in Montreal and, several years ago, stopped a runaway by the name of Jean-Paul Beaubier from stealing from him. He took the young Beaubier under his wing and guided him through life, introducing him to skiing and helping him become more comfortable with himself. Eventually, Beaubier went on his way in life, only occasionally visiting.

On one of those visits, he was introduced to Danielle, Raymonde's daughter, whom he had never heard of. He also had surprise introductions to make, introducing Raymonde to his long-lost sister. However, their joyous reunion was cut short when a local crime lord, Deadly Ernest used his death touch to kill Raymonde and then kidnapped Aurora. Northstar, working with the vigilante Nemesis was able to defeat Ernest. However, Aurora then shocked him by revealing that Danielle had betrayed her father by allying herself with Ernest. Danielle was captured and turned over to the police.
name: Raymonde Belmonde

description:
Origin

Amber Grant was a young 'no-nonsese' woman whom lived in New York City with her roomate, Ruth Hart. Amber was a photographer for the Daily Buge. Despite both of their incomes, the roommates had an appartement in one of the less pleasant neighbourhoods in New York City.

Creation

Amber Grant was created by Steve Gerber, Mary Skrenes and Jim Mooney and first appeared in Omega the Unknown Vol.1 issue 1 (1976).

Major Story Arcs

Meeting James-Michael Starling

When Amber heard that her roommate Ruth had volunteerd to take in a young boy from the hospital, she was at first very relunctand. Amber however soon took a liking to the young boy and took him out to see the city, also wisecracking and learning him about the facts of living in the mean streets of New York City. It however soon became apparent that Jame-Michael had a strange conncetion to a mysterious superhero named Omega the Unknown. Because of this, Amber, Ruth and the boy found themeselves in strange and sometimes dangerous situations. After the seeming death of Omega the Unknown, Amber and Ruth encountered the superhero team known as the Defenders and joined them for some time, but they have not been seen since.

deck: Sister of Sabretooth. She worked as an animal handler for Hugo the Great's circus where she met Logan (Wolverine).
description:
Origin

The youngest of the Creed children, she was tortured by her brother Saul at their brother Victor's orders. Later, wanting to know the extent of her regenerative powers, she asked Saul to drip acid on her face. She discovered her powers had a limit when the left side of her face became permanently disfigured.

Creation

Clara Creed was created by Kieron Gillen and Adam Kubert and first appeared in Origin II issue 2 (2014).

Major Story Arcs

Meeting the Wolverine

As adults, Clara and Saul work for Hugo Haversham at his circus, where they meet Logan. Clara sees the man in the bewildered beast, as Logan is presented to the circus audience. She tries to civilize him, but Saul isn't happy with their relationship. He rats Logan's location out to Nathaniel Essex, who immediatly sends his Marauders to capture Logan. In the ensuing battle, Logan accidently stabs Clara. Thinking her dead, Saul offers Logan revenge on Essex. In Essex' lab, Essex tells Logan that Saul had sold him out. Confronting Saul with this fact, Clara turns out to be alive. Being Saul's sister, she has the same regenerative abilities that her brothers Saul and Victor have. Seeing no way out, Logan kills Saul by drowning him. Angered and grieved, Clara dismisses Logan, claiming she never wants to see him again.
name: Clara
